      • createReader

        default java.io.Reader createReader(java.lang.String pathToFile)
                             throws java.io.IOException
        Creates a Reader based on pathToFile. First, it tries to create a FileReader by creating a file. If a FileNotFoundException is encountered, it creates a URL from the pathToFile and creates a InputStreamReader based on URL.openStream().
        Parameters:
        pathToFile - The path to the file
        Returns:
        A Reader with the information of the file
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If the FileReader cannot be created or Url.openStream() fails to open the stream.
